ion for common setup issues\n202: \n203: ### T022: Concepts and terminology documentation\n204: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/introduction/concepts.md`\n205: - [ ] Define core concepts (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, Session, Sandbox)\n206: - [ ] Explain key terminology (Router, WorkloadManager, PicoD, Controller)\n207: - [ ] Document session lifecycle concepts\n208: - [ ] Explain resource management concepts\n209: - [ ] Add glossary of terms\n210: \n211: ### T023: Deployment overview documentation\n212: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/overview.md`\n213: - [ ] Document deployment architecture options (single cluster, multi-cluster)\n214: - [ ] List and explain deployment prerequisites\n215: - - [ ] Document required components and their versions\n216: - [ ] Provide deployment checklist\n217: - [ ] Add deployment architecture diagram\n218: \n219: ### T024: Kubernetes deployment documentation\n220: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/kubernetes.md`\n221: - [ ] Document Helm Chart usage\n222:   - [ ] Document installation commands\n223:   - [ ] Document values.yaml configuration\n224:   - [ ] Document custom configuration examples\n225: - [ ] Document manual deployment steps (optional)\n226: - [ ] Document Redis deployment requirements\n227: - [ ] Document upgrade procedures\n228: - [ ] Document rollback procedures\n229: - [ ] Add Kubernetes deployment diagram\n230: \n231: ### T025: Configuration reference documentation\n232: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/deployment/configuration.md`\n233: - [ ] Document WorkloadManager configuration options\n234: - [ ] Document Router configuration options\n235: - [ ] Document Redis/Valkey configuration\n236: - [ ] Document environment variables\n237: - [ ] Provide configuration examples for different scenarios\n238: - [ ] Document security configuration (JWT keys, RBAC)\n239: \n240: ### T026: Monitoring documentation\n241: - [ ] Create `docs/docs/operations/monitoring.md`\n242: - [ ] List and describe all available metrics\n243: - [ ] Document