{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775900810898,"sessionID":"ses_28410712dffe2YTvwM8OaDTSPJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7befde67001NTxir16gjS5FNi","messageID":"msg_d7befc1d2001KnNOe1iAgIMlOl","sessionID":"ses_28410712dffe2YTvwM8OaDTSPJ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-882a376d100843e5b39793a618184613","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/agentcube/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/agentcube/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Design: AR-043 — AgentCube Architecture Design and API Documentation\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native AI agent runtime platform that provides tools for building, deploying, and managing AI agent workloads. The platform consists of a Python SDK, CLI tools, and Kubernetes custom resources that together enable a complete agent development lifecycle.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### High-Level Architecture\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                         Developer Layer                              │\n14: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐              │\n15: │  │   Python SDK │  │   CLI Tools  │  │  kubectl plg │              │\n16: │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘              │\n17: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n18:                               │\n19:                               ▼\n20: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n21: │                      AgentCube Platform                              │\n22: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n23: │  │                    Control Plane                              │  │\n24: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐      │  │\n25: │  │  │ Workload Mgr │  │ Controller   │  │ CRD Manager  │      │  │\n26: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘      │  │\n27: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n28: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n29: │  │                    Data Plane                                 │  │\n30: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐      │  │\n31: │  │  │    Router    │  │    Picod     │  │ Session Store│      │  │\n32: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘      │  │\n33: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n34: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n35:                               │\n36:                               ▼\n37: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n38: │                      Kubernetes Cluster                              │\n39: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐              │\n40: │  │ AgentRuntime │  │CodeInterpreter│  │Agent Workload│              │\n41: │  │    CRDs      │  │    CRDs       │  │   Pods       │              │\n42: │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘              │\n43: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n44: ```\n45: \n46: ### Component Architecture\n47: \n48: #### Python SDK Layer\n49: \n50: ```\n51: agentcube/\n52: ├── __init__.py\n53: ├── agent_runtime.py           # Agent runtime client\n54: ├── code_interpreter.py        # Code interpreter client\n55: ├── exceptions.py              # Exception hierarchy\n56: ├── clients/\n57: │   ├── control_plane.py       # Control plane API client\n58: │   ├── agent_runtime_data_plane.py    # Agent runtime data plane client\n59: │   └── code_interpreter_data_plane.py # Code interpreter data plane client\n60: └── utils/\n61:     ├── http.py                # HTTP session management\n62:     ├── log.py                 # Logging utilities\n63:     └── utils.py               # Common utilities\n64: ```\n65: \n66: #### CLI Layer\n67: \n68: ```\n69: cmd/cli/agentcube/\n70: ├── cli/\n71: │   └── main.py                # CLI entry point with Typer\n72: ├── runtime/\n73: │   ├── pack_runtime.py        # Packaging logic\n74: │   ├── build_runtime.py       # Image building logic\n75: │   ├── publish_runtime.py     # Publishing logic\n76: │   ├── invoke_runtime.py      # Invocation logic\n77: │   └── status_runtime.py      # Status query logic\n78: ├── providers/\n79: │   ├── base.py                # Base provider interface\n80: │   ├── k8s_provider.py        # Kubernetes provider\n81: │   └── agentcube_provider.py  # AgentCube provider\n82: ├── services/\n83: │   ├── metadata_service.py    # Metadata management\n84: │   └── docker_service.py      # Docker operations\n85: └── models/\n86:     └── pack_models.py         # Data models\n87: ```\n88: \n89: #### Platform Layer\n90: \n91: ```\n92: cmd/agentcube/\n93: └── main.go                    # Controller manager entry point\n94: \n95: pkg/\n96: ├── controller/                # Kubernetes controllers\n97: ├── router/                    # Request routing\n98: ├── store/                     # Session storage\n99: └── picod/                     # Code execution\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ## Data Structures\n103: \n104: ### Python SDK Data Structures\n105: \n106: #### AgentRuntimeClient\n107: \n108: ```python\n109: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n110:     \"\"\"Client for Agent Runtime invocation.\"\"\"\n111:     \n112:     agent_name: str\n113:     namespace: str\n114:     router_url: str\n115:     session_id: str\n116:     timeout: int\n117:     connect_timeout: float\n118:     verbose: bool\n119: ```\n120: \n121: #### CodeInterpreterClient\n122: \n123: ```python\n124: class CodeInterpreterClient:\n125:     \"\"\"Main client for Code Interpreter session management.\"\"\"\n126:     \n127:     name: str\n128:     namespace: str\n129:     ttl: int\n130:     workload_manager_url: str\n131:     router_url: str\n132:     auth_token: str\n133:     session_id: str\n134:     verbose: bool\n135: ```\n136: \n137: #### AgentMetadata (Pydantic Model)\n138: \n139: ```python\n140: class AgentMetadata(BaseModel):\n141:     \"\"\"Agent metadata model.\"\"\"\n142:     \n143:     agent_name: str\n144:     description: str | None\n145:     language: str = \"python\"\n146:     entrypoint: str\n147:     port: int = 8080\n148:     build_mode: str = \"local\"\n149:     region: str | None\n150:     version: str | None\n151:     image: dict[str, Any] | None\n152:     auth: dict[str, Any] | None\n153:     requirements_file: str | None = \"requirements.txt\"\n154:     registry_url: str | None\n155:     registry_username: str | None\n156:     registry_password: str | None\n157:     agent_endpoint: str | None\n158:     workload_manager_url: str | None\n159:     router_url: str | None\n160:     readiness_probe_path: str | None\n161:     readiness_probe_port: int | None\n162:     agent_id: str | None\n163:     session_id: str | None\n164:     k8s_deployment: dict[str, Any] | None\n165: ```\n166: \n167: #### DeploymentResult\n168: \n169: ```python\n170: @dataclass\n171: class DeploymentResult:\n172:     \"\"\"Deployment result data class.\"\"\"\n173:     \n174:     status: ProviderStatus\n175:     agent_name: str\n176:     namespace: str\n177:     resource_url: str | None\n178:     metadata: dict[str, Any]\n179:     error: str | None\n180: ```\n181: \n182: #### AgentStatus\n183: \n184: ```python\n185: @dataclass\n186: class AgentStatus:\n187:     \"\"\"Agent status data class.\"\"\"\n188:     \n189:     status: ProviderStatus\n190:     agent_name: str\n191:     namespace: str\n192:     replicas: int | None\n193:     ready_replicas: int | None\n194:     available_replicas: int | None\n195:     resource_type: str | None\n196:     metadata: dict[str, Any]\n197:     error: str | None\n198: ```\n199: \n200: #### ProviderStatus\n201: \n202: ```python\n203: class ProviderStatus(str, Enum):\n204:     \"\"\"Provider status enumeration.\"\"\"\n205:     \n206:     PENDING = \"pending\"\n207:     DEPLOYING = \"deploying\"\n208:     RUNNING = \"running\"\n209:     FAILED = \"failed\"\n210:     NOT_FOUND = \"not_found\"\n211:     ERROR = \"error\"\n212: ```\n213: \n214: ### Kubernetes Custom Resources\n215: \n216: #### AgentRuntime CRD\n217: \n218: ```yaml\n219: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n220: kind: AgentRuntime\n221: metadata:\n222:   name: example-agent\n223:   namespace: default\n224: spec:\n225:   maxSessionDuration: 8h\n226:   podTemplate:\n227:     metadata:\n228:       labels:\n229:         app: example-agent\n230:     spec:\n231:       containers:\n232:       - name: agent\n233:         image: example/agent:latest\n234:         ports:\n235:         - containerPort: 8080\n236: status:\n237:   conditions:\n238:   - type: Ready\n239:     status: \"True\"\n240:     lastTransitionTime: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n241:     reason: DeploymentReady\n242:     message: Deployment is ready\n243:   observedGeneration: 1\n244: ```\n245: \n246: #### CodeInterpreter CRD\n247: \n248: ```yaml\n249: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n250: kind: CodeInterpreter\n251: metadata:\n252:   name: example-interpreter\n253:   namespace: default\n254: spec:\n255:   image: python:3.10-slim\n256:   runtime: python\n257:   timeout: 5m\n258:   resources:\n259:     limits:\n260:       cpu: \"2\"\n261:       memory: \"2Gi\"\n262:     requests:\n263:       cpu: \"1\"\n264:       memory: \"1Gi\"\n265:   enabledPackages:\n266:   - numpy\n267:   - pandas\n268:   env:\n269:   - name: PYTHONPATH\n270:     value: /usr/local/lib/python3.10/site-packages\n271: status:\n272:   ready: true\n273:   conditions:\n274:   - type: Ready\n275:     status: \"True\"\n276:     lastTransitionTime: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n277:   observedGeneration: 1\n278: ```\n279: \n280: ## API Contracts\n281: \n282: ### Control Plane API\n283: \n284: #### Create Session\n285: \n286: **Endpoint**: `POST /v1/code-interpreter`\n287: \n288: **Request Body**:\n289: ```json\n290: {\n291:   \"name\": \"my-interpreter\",\n292:   \"namespace\": \"default\",\n293:   \"ttl\": 3600,\n294:   \"metadata\": {\n295:     \"labels\": {\n296:       \"env\": \"dev\"\n297:     }\n298:   }\n299: }\n300: ```\n301: \n302: **Response**:\n303: ```json\n304: {\n305:   \"sessionId\": \"uuid-session-id\",\n306:   \"status\": \"created\"\n307: }\n308: ```\n309: \n310: **Headers**:\n311: - `Authorization`: `Bearer <token>`\n312: \n313: #### Delete Session\n314: \n315: **Endpoint**: `DELETE /v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{sessionId}`\n316: \n317: **Response**:\n318: - Status Code: `204 No Content`\n319: \n320: **Headers**:\n321: - `Authorization`: `Bearer <token>`\n322: \n323: ### Data Plane API (Agent Runtime)\n324: \n325: #### Bootstrap Session\n326: \n327: **Endpoint**: `GET /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agentName}/invocations/`\n328: \n329: **Response Headers**:\n330: - `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n331: \n332: **Response Body**: Empty\n333: \n334: #### Invoke Agent\n335: \n336: **Endpoint**: `POST /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agentName}/invocations/`\n337: \n338: **Request Headers**:\n339: - `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n340: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n341: \n342: **Request Body**:\n343: ```json\n344: {\n345:   \"message\": \"Hello, agent!\",\n346:   \"context\": {\n347:     \"user\": \"test-user\"\n348:   }\n349: }\n350: ```\n351: \n352: **Response Body**:\n353: ```json\n354: {\n355:   \"response\": \"Hello! How can I help you today?\",\n356:   \"status\": \"success\"\n357: }\n358: ```\n359: \n360: ### Data Plane API (Code Interpreter)\n361: \n362: #### Execute Command\n363: \n364: **Endpoint**: `POST /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{crName}/invocations/api/execute`\n365: \n366: **Request Headers**:\n367: - `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n368: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n369: \n370: **Request Body**:\n371: ```json\n372: {\n373:   \"command\": [\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('Hello')\"],\n374:   \"timeout\": \"30s\"\n375: }\n376: ```\n377: \n378: **Response Body**:\n379: ```json\n380: {\n381:   \"stdout\": \"Hello\\n\",\n382:   \"stderr\": \"\",\n383:   \"exit_code\": 0\n384: }\n385: ```\n386: \n387: #### Write File\n388: \n389: **Endpoint**: `POST /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{crName}/invocations/api/files`\n390: \n391: **Request Headers**:\n392: - `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n393: - `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n394: \n395: **Request Body**:\n396: ```json\n397: {\n398:   \"path\": \"/workspace/test.py\",\n399:   \"content\": \"base64-encoded-content\",\n400:   \"mode\": \"0644\"\n401: }\n402: ```\n403: \n404: **Response**: Status `200 OK`\n405: \n406: #### List Files\n407: \n408: **Endpoint**: `GET /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{crName}/invocations/api/files`\n409: \n410: **Request Headers**:\n411: - `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n412: \n413: **Query Parameters**:\n414: - `path`: Directory path (default: \".\")\n415: \n416: **Response Body**:\n417: ```json\n418: {\n419:   \"files\": [\n420:     {\n421:       \"name\": \"test.py\",\n422:       \"path\": \"/workspace/test.py\",\n423:       \"size\": 1024,\n424:       \"mode\": \"0644\"\n425:     }\n426:   ],\n427:   \"directories\": [\n428:     {\n429:       \"name\": \"data\",\n430:       \"path\": \"/workspace/data\"\n431:     }\n432:   ]\n433: }\n434: ```\n435: \n436: #### Download File\n437: \n438: **Endpoint**: `GET /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{crName}/invocations/api/files/{path}`\n439: \n440: **Request Headers**:\n441: - `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n442: \n443: **Response**: File content (binary stream)\n444: \n445: #### Upload File\n446: \n447: **Endpoint**: `POST /v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{crName}/invocations/api/files`\n448: \n449: **Request Headers**:\n450: - `x-agentcube-session-id`: Session UUID\n451: \n452: **Request Body**: `multipart/form-data`\n453: - `file`: File content\n454: - `path`: Target path\n455: - `mode`: File permissions (default: \"0644\")\n456: \n457: **Response**: Status `200 OK`\n458: \n459: ## Error Handling\n460: \n461: ### Exception Hierarchy\n462: \n463: ```python\n464: # Base exception\n465: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n466:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK.\"\"\"\n467:     pass\n468: \n469: # Command execution errors\n470: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n471:     \"\"\"Raised when command execution fails.\"\"\"\n472:     \n473:     def __init__(self, exit_code: int, stderr: str, command: str | None = None):\n474:         self.exit_code = exit_code\n475:         self.stderr = stderr\n476:         self.command = command\n477:         super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n478: \n479: # Session management errors\n480: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n481:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails.\"\"\"\n482:     pass\n483: \n484: # Data plane operation errors\n485: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n486:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail.\"\"\"\n487:     pass\n488: ```\n489: \n490: ### Error Response Format\n491: \n492: **Standard Error Response**:\n493: ```json\n494: {\n495:   \"error\": {\n496:     \"code\": \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\",\n497:     \"message\": \"Session ID 'xxx' not found or expired\",\n498:     \"details\": {\n499:       \"sessionId\": \"xxx\",\n500:       \"ttl\": 3600\n501:     }\n502:   },\n503:   \"requestId\": \"uuid-request-id\"\n504: }\n505: ```\n506: \n507: ### HTTP Status Codes\n508: \n509: | Status Code | Description | Usage |\n510: |-------------|-------------|-------|\n511: | 200 | OK | Successful operation |\n512: | 201 | Created | Resource created successfully |\n513: | 204 | No Content | Successful operation with no response body |\n514: | 400 | Bad Request | Invalid request parameters |\n515: | 401 | Unauthorized | Missing or invalid authentication |\n516: | 403 | Forbidden | Insufficient permissions |\n517: | 404 | Not Found | Resource not found |\n518: | 409 | Conflict | Resource already exists |\n519: | 429 | Too Many Requests | Rate limit exceeded |\n520: | 500 | Internal Server Error | Server-side error |\n521: | 503 | Service Unavailable | Service temporarily unavailable |\n522: \n523: ### Error Codes\n524: \n525: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n526: |------|-------------|-------------|\n527: | `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Session ID not found or expired |\n528: | `SESSION_ALREADY_EXISTS` | 409 | Session with same name already exists |\n529: | `INVALID_SESSION_ID` | 400 | Invalid session ID format |\n530: | `COMMAND_EXECUTION_FAILED` | 500 | Command execution failed |\n531: | `TIMEOUT_EXCEEDED` | 504 | Operation timed out |\n532: | `UNAUTHORIZED_ACCESS` | 403 | Insufficient permissions |\n533: | `INVALID_REQUEST_BODY` | 400 | Invalid request JSON |\n534: | `UNSUPPORTED_LANGUAGE` | 400 | Unsupported programming language |\n535: | `FILE_NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Requested file not found |\n536: | `INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES` | 503 | Insufficient cluster resources |\n537: \n538: ### Retry Strategy\n539: \n540: **Exponential Backoff**:\n541: - Initial delay: 1 second\n542: - Maximum delay: 30 seconds\n543: - Maximum attempts: 3\n544: - Backoff factor: 2.0\n545: \n546: ```python\n547: from agentcube.providers.retry import retry_on_exception\n548: \n549: @retry_on_exception(\n550:     max_attempts=3,\n551:     delay=2.0,\n552:     exceptions=(ApiException,)\n553: )\n554: def _wait_for_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int) -> None:\n555:     \"\"\"Wait for deployment to be ready with retry logic.\"\"\"\n556:     # Implementation\n557:     pass\n558: ```\n559: \n560: ## Testing Strategy\n561: \n562: ### Unit Testing\n563: \n564: #### Python SDK Tests\n565: \n566: **Test Structure**:\n567: ```\n568: agentcube/tests/\n569: ├── __init__.py\n570: ├── test_agent_runtime.py\n571: ├── test_code_interpreter.py\n572: ├── test_clients/\n573: │   ├── test_control_plane.py\n574: │   ├── test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py\n575: │   └── test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py\n576: └── fixtures/\n577:     ├── mock_responses.py\n578:     └── test_data.py\n579: ```\n580: \n581: **Test Framework**: `pytest`\n582: \n583: **Key Test Areas**:\n584: 1. Client initialization and configuration\n585: 2. Session lifecycle management\n586: 3. Command execution and error handling\n587: 4. File operations (write, read, upload, download)\n588: 5. HTTP request/response handling\n589: 6. Timeout and retry logic\n590: \n591: **Example Test**:\n592: ```python\n593: import pytest\n594: from unittest.mock import Mock, patch\n595: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n596: \n597: @pytest.fixture\n598: def mock_response():\n599:     response = Mock()\n600:     response.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"test-session-id\"}\n601:     response.headers = {}\n602:     return response\n603: \n604: def test_create_session(mock_response):\n605:     with patch('requests.Session.post', return_value=mock_response):\n606:         client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n607:             name=\"test-interpreter\",\n608:             namespace=\"default\",\n609:             router_url=\"http://test-router\"\n610:         )\n611:         assert client.session_id == \"test-session-id\"\n612: \n613: def test_execute_command_error():\n614:     client = CodeInterpreterClient(\n615:         name=\"test-interpreter\",\n616:         namespace=\"default\",\n617:         router_url=\"http://test-router\",\n618:         session_id=\"test-session-id\"\n619:     )\n620:     \n621:     mock_response = Mock()\n622:     mock_response.json.return_value = {\n623:         \"stdout\": \"\",\n624:         \"stderr\": \"Command failed\",\n625:         \"exit_code\": 1\n626:     }\n627:     \n628:     with patch('requests.Session.post', return_value=mock_response):\n629:         with pytest.raises(CommandExecutionError) as exc_info:\n630:             client.execute_command(\"false\")\n631:         assert exc_info.value.exit_code == 1\n632: ```\n633: \n634: #### CLI Tests\n635: \n636: **Test Structure**:\n637: ```\n638: cmd/cli/agentcube/tests/\n639: ├── __init__.py\n640: ├── test_cli.py\n641: ├── test_runtime/\n642: │   ├── test_pack_runtime.py\n643: │   ├── test_build_runtime.py\n644: │   ├── test_publish_runtime.py\n645: │   ├── test_invoke_runtime.py\n646: │   └── test_status_runtime.py\n647: ├── test_providers/\n648: │   ├── test_base_provider.py\n649: │   ├── test_k8s_provider.py\n650: │   └── test_agentcube_provider.py\n651: └── test_services/\n652:     ├── test_metadata_service.py\n653:     └── test_docker_service.py\n654: ```\n655: \n656: **Test Framework**: `pytest` with `typer.testing`\n657: \n658: **Key Test Areas**:\n659: 1. CLI command parsing and validation\n660: 2. Runtime execution flow\n661: 3. Provider deployment and status\n662: 4. Metadata management\n663: 5. Docker operations (mocked)\n664: 6. Error handling and user feedback\n665: \n666: **Example Test**:\n667: ```python\n668: from typer.testing import CliRunner\n669: from agentcube.cli.main import app\n670: \n671: runner = CliRunner()\n672: \n673: def test_pack_command():\n674:     result = runner.invoke(app, [\n675:         \"pack\",\n676:         \"--workspace\", \"tests/fixtures/sample-agent\",\n677:         \"--agent-name\", \"test-agent\"\n678:     ])\n679:     assert result.exit_code == 0\n680:     assert \"Successfully packaged agent\" in result.stdout\n681: \n682: def test_pack_command_invalid_workspace():\n683:     result = runner.invoke(app, [\n684:         \"pack\",\n685:         \"--workspace\", \"/nonexistent/path\"\n686:     ])\n687:     assert result.exit_code == 1\n688:     assert \"Error\" in result.stdout\n689: ```\n690: \n691: ### Integration Testing\n692: \n693: **Test Structure**:\n694: ```\n695: manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/integration/\n696: ├── test_token_automount.sh\n697: ├── test_no_wildcard_permissions.sh\n698: ├── test_least_privilege.sh\n699: ├── test_workload_manager_permissions.sh\n700: ├── test_custom_rbac_deployment.sh\n701: ├── test_router_permissions.sh\n702: ├── test_existing_serviceaccount.sh\n703: ├── controller-manager_test.yaml\n704: ├── router_test.yaml\n705: ├── workload-manager_test.yaml\n706: └── rbac_test.yaml\n707: ```\n708: \n709: **Test Framework**: Bash scripts + Kubernetes client\n710: \n711: **Key Test Areas**:\n712: 1. RBAC permissions verification\n713: 2. Service account token mounting\n714: 3. Custom resource creation and reconciliation\n715: 4. Pod lifecycle management\n716: 5. Network policies\n717: 6. Resource quotas\n718: \n719: **Example Test**:\n720: ```bash\n721: #!/bin/bash\n722: set -e\n723: \n724: echo \"Testing RBAC permissions for Controller Manager...\"\n725: \n726: # Create test namespace\n727: kubectl create namespace test-rbac-$(date +%s) || true\n728: \n729: # Deploy controller-manager with limited permissions\n730: helm install agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube \\\n731:   --namespace test-rbac \\\n732:   --set controllerManager.enabled=true \\\n733:   --set controllerManager.serviceAccount.create=true\n734: \n735: # Verify permissions\n736: kubectl auth can-i get agentruntimes --namespace test-rbac\n737: kubectl auth can-i update codeinterpreters --namespace test-rbac\n738: \n739: # Clean up\n740: helm uninstall agentcube --namespace test-rbac\n741: kubectl delete namespace test-rbac\n742: \n743: echo \"RBAC test passed!\"\n744: ```\n745: \n746: ### End-to-End Testing\n747: \n748: **Test Scenarios**:\n749: \n750: 1. **Complete Agent Lifecycle**:\n751:    - Create agent workspace\n752:    - Pack workspace\n753:    - Build image\n754:    - Publish to Kubernetes\n755:    - Invoke agent\n756:    - Query status\n757:    - Delete agent\n758: \n759: 2. **Code Interpreter Session**:\n760:    - Create interpreter session\n761:    - Execute commands\n762:    - Write/read files\n763:    - Upload/download files\n764:    - Delete session\n765: \n766: 3. **Agent Runtime Invocation**:\n767:    - Bootstrap session\n768:    - Send multiple requests\n769:    - Handle errors\n770:    - Session expiration\n771: \n772: **Test Framework**: Python with `pytest` + `kind` (Kubernetes in Docker)\n773: \n774: **Example Test**:\n775: ```python\n776: import pytest\n777: from pathlib import Path\n778: from agentcube import CodeInterpreterClient\n779: from agentcube.cli.main import app\n780: from typer.testing import CliRunner\n781: \n782: @pytest.mark.e2e\n783: def test_complete_agent_lifecycle():\n784:     runner = CliRunner()\n785:     \n786:     # 1. Create workspace\n787:     workspace = Path(\"/tmp/test-agent\")\n788:     workspace.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n789:     (workspace / \"main.py\").write_text('print(\"Hello, World!\")')\n790:     \n791:     # 2. Pack\n792:     result = runner.invoke(app, [\"pack\", \"--workspace\", str(workspace)])\n793:     assert result.exit_code == 0\n794:     \n795:     # 3. Build\n796:     result = runner.invoke(app, [\"build\", \"--workspace\", str(workspace)])\n797:     assert result.exit_code == 0\n798:     \n799:     # 4. Publish\n800:     result = runner.invoke(app, [\n801:         \"publish\",\n802:         \"--workspace\", str(workspace),\n803:         \"--provider\", \"k8s\",\n804:         \"--namespace\", \"test-e2e\"\n805:     ])\n806:     assert result.exit_code == 0\n807:     \n808:     # 5. Invoke\n809:     result = runner.invoke(app, [\n810:         \"invoke\",\n811:         \"--workspace\", str(workspace),\n812:         '--payload', '{\"message\": \"test\"}',\n813:         \"--provider\", \"k8s\"\n814:     ])\n815:     assert result.exit_code == 0\n816:     \n817:     # 6. Status\n818:     result = runner.invoke(app, [\n819:         \"status\",\n820:         \"--workspace\", str(workspace),\n821:         \"--provider\", \"k8s\"\n822:     ])\n823:     assert result.exit_code == 0\n824:     assert \"running\" in result.stdout.lower()\n825:     \n826:     # Clean up\n827:     import subprocess\n828:     subprocess.run([\"kubectl\", \"delete\", \"deployment\", \"test-agent\", \"-n\", \"test-e2e\"])\n829: ```\n830: \n831: ### Performance Testing\n832: \n833: **Metrics to Monitor**:\n834: 1. API response times (p50, p95, p99)\n835: 2. Session creation latency\n836: 3. Command execution duration\n837: 4. File upload/download throughput\n838: 5. Memory usage\n839: 6. CPU utilization\n840: 7. Concurrent request handling\n841: \n842: **Tools**:\n843: - `locust` for load testing\n844: - `prometheus` + `grafana` for monitoring\n845: - `pprof` for profiling\n846: \n847: **Example Locust Test**:\n848: ```python\n849: from locust import HttpUser, task, between\n850: \n851: class AgentCubeUser(HttpUser):\n852:     wait_time = between(1, 3)\n853:     \n854:     def on_start(self):\n855:         self.session_id = self.create_session()\n856:     \n857:     @task\n858:     def execute_command(self):\n859:         self.client.post(\n860:             f\"/v1/namespaces/default/code-interpreters/test/invocations/api/execute\",\n861:             json={\"command\": [\"echo\", \"hello\"], \"timeout\": \"10s\"},\n862:             headers={\"x-agentcube-session-id\": self.session_id}\n863:         )\n864:     \n865:     def create_session(self):\n866:         response = self.client.post(\n867:             \"/v1/code-interpreter\",\n868:             json={\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"default\", \"ttl\": 3600}\n869:         )\n870:         return response.json()[\"sessionId\"]\n871: ```\n872: \n873: ### Test Coverage Goals\n874: \n875: | Component | Unit Tests | Integration Tests | E2E Tests |\n876: |-----------|------------|-------------------|-----------|\n877: | Python SDK | 80%+ | N/A | N/A |\n878: | CLI | 70%+ | N/A | N/A |\n879: | Providers | 75%+ | 50%+ | N/A |\n880: | Services | 80%+ | N/A | N/A |\n881: | Controllers | 60%+ | 70%+ | 40%+ |\n882: | Router | 70%+ | 60%+ | 40%+ |\n883: | Store | 80%+ | 60%+ | 40%+ |\n884: | Picod | 75%+ | 60%+ | 40%+ |\n885: \n886: ### Continuous Integration\n887: \n888: **CI Pipeline**:\n889: 1. **Linting**: `flake8`, `black`, `isort`, `golint`, `gofmt`\n890: 2. **Static Analysis**: `mypy`, `pylint`, `go vet`\n891: 3. **Unit Tests**: Run with coverage reporting\n892: 4. **Integration Tests**: Run against `kind` cluster\n893: 5. **E2E Tests**: Run on test environment\n894: 6. **Security Scans**: `trivy`, `gosec`, `bandit`\n895: 7. **Build**: Docker images, CLI binaries\n896: 8. **Publish**: Push to registry, GitHub releases\n897: \n898: **Pre-commit Hooks**:\n899: ```yaml\n900: repos:\n901:   - repo: https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks\n902:     hooks:\n903:       - id: trailing-whitespace\n904:       - id: end-of-file-fixer\n905:       - id: check-yaml\n906:       - id: check-added-large-files\n907:   - repo: https://github.com/psf/black\n908:     hooks:\n909:       - id: black\n910:   - repo: https://github.com/pycqa/isort\n911:     hooks:\n912:       - id: isort\n913:   - repo: https://github.com/pycqa/flake8\n914:     hooks:\n915:       - id: flake8\n916: ```\n917: \n918: ## Security Considerations\n919: \n920: ### Authentication & Authorization\n921: \n922: 1. **Kubernetes Service Accounts**: Use RBAC for API authentication\n923: 2. **JWT Tokens**: Session-based authentication with time-limited tokens\n924: 3. **Network Policies**: Restrict pod-to-pod communication\n925: 4. **Secrets Management**: Use Kubernetes Secrets or external secret stores\n926: \n927: ### Input Validation\n928: \n929: 1. **Session ID Validation**: UUID format checking\n930: 2. **Command Validation**: Whitelist allowed commands\n931: 3. **File Path Validation**: Prevent directory traversal\n932: 4. **Payload Size Limits**: Maximum request body size\n933: \n934: ### Rate Limiting\n935: \n936: 1. **Request Throttling**: Per-session and per-user limits\n937: 2. **Resource Quotas**: CPU, memory, and storage limits\n938: 3. **Concurrency Limits**: Maximum concurrent sessions per user\n939: \n940: ### Audit Logging\n941: \n942: 1. **API Access Logs**: All API calls with timestamps\n943: 2. **Session Lifecycle Logs**: Creation, updates, deletion\n944: 3. **Command Execution Logs**: All commands executed in sessions\n945: 4. **Error Logs**: All errors with stack traces\n946: \n947: ## Deployment Strategy\n948: \n949: ### Helm Chart\n950: \n951: The platform is deployed using Helm charts with configurable values:\n952: \n953: ```yaml\n954: # values.yaml\n955: controllerManager:\n956:   enabled: true\n957:   replicas: 2\n958:   image:\n959:     repository: agentcube/controller-manager\n960:     tag: v1.0.0\n961: \n962: router:\n963:   enabled: true\n964:   replicas: 3\n965:   image:\n966:     repository: agentcube/router\n967:     tag: v1.0.0\n968: \n969: workloadManager:\n970:   enabled: true\n971:   replicas: 2\n972:   image:\n973:     repository: agentcube/workload-manager\n974:     tag: v1.0.0\n975: \n976: storage:\n977:   type: redis\n978:   redis:\n979:     host: redis.default.svc.cluster.local\n980:     port: 6379\n981:     password: \"\"\n982: ```\n983: \n984: ### Upgrade Strategy\n985: \n986: 1. **Rolling Updates**: Zero-downtime deployments\n987: 2. **Database Migrations**: Versioned schema changes\n988: 3. **Backward Compatibility**: Support old API versions\n989: 4. **Blue-Green Deployments**: Gradual traffic shifting\n990: \n991: ### Monitoring & Observability\n992: \n993: 1. **Metrics**: Prometheus metrics for all components\n994: 2. **Logging**: Structured logs with correlation IDs\n995: 3. **Tracing**: Distributed tracing with OpenTelemetry\n996: 4. **Health Checks**: readiness and liveness probes\n997: 5. **Alerting**: PagerDuty/Slack integration for critical failures\n998: \n999: ## Future Enhancements\n1000: \n1001: 1. **Multi-Cluster Support**: Deploy agents across multiple clusters\n1002: 2. **GPU Support**: GPU-accelerated code execution\n1003: 3. **Custom Runtime Support**: Support additional language runtimes\n1004: 4. **Session Persistence**: Long-running session state management\n1005: 5. **Collaboration Features**: Multi-user session sharing\n1006: 6. **Cost Optimization**: Resource usage optimization and billing\n1007: 7. **Advanced Security**: Fine-grained access control and audit trails\n\n(End of file - total 1007 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Design: AR-043 — AgentCube Architecture Design and API Documentation\n\n## Overview\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native AI agent runtime platform that provides tools for building, deploying, and managing AI agent workloads. The platform consists of a Python SDK, CLI tools, and Kubernetes custom resources that together enable a complete agent development lifecycle.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Developer Layer                              │\n│  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐              │\n│  │   Python SDK │  │   CLI Tools  │  │  kubectl plg │              │\n│  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/agentcube/design.md","time":{"start":1775900810885,"end":1775900810895}}}}
